Ad Text:
Life Days are the Leidos way of recognising that we all need extra time to take care of life. By working slightly more than the minimum weekly hours (2 hours per week for full-timers), you can accrue up to 12 days of leave per year.
Leidos Life Hub provides access to discount offers or cashback rewards with over 400 Australian and International retailers.
Due to the nature of the role, you must be an Australian Citizen and hold an active NV-1 AGVSA Security Clearance.

Our team feel Leidos is a great place to work. Learn more about our culture and benefits by visiting us here https://www.leidos.com/company/global/australia/careers

Do Work That Matters

Leidos Australia delivers IT and airborne solutions that protect and advance the Australian way of life.  Our 2000 local experts, backed by our global experience and network of partners, are working to solve the world's toughest challenges in government, intelligence, defence, aviation, border protection and health markets.

Expression of Interest

We anticipate an increase in work to support upcoming projects and are proactively building a pipeline of talented professionals to meet this demand.

Your New Role and Responsibilities

At Leidos Australia, our Matrix Engineering Team is a hub of technical excellence, supporting mission-critical programs across Defence, Intelligence, and Federal Government portfolios.

As a Midrange Engineer, you will:

Manage and optimize VMware vCenter, ESXi clusters, vSAN, and related technologies.
Translate customer requirements into detailed designs and supporting services for complex PaaS solutions.
Develop and maintain automation for provisioning and orchestration using Ansible/Terraform; create reusable IaC modules and templates.
Automate vCenter operations such as VM provisioning, patching, compliance, and policy enforcement.
Produce technical documentation and provide subject matter expertise to resolve complex technical issues.

What You'll Bring to Make an Impact
 

Extensive experience with VMware VCF solutions, plus integration with networks and other services.
Demonstrated experience in both programming and infrastructure, with proficiency in automation tools like Ansible and Terraform.
Proficiency in Microsoft Windows Server (2012-2022), Active Directory, DNS, DHCP, and DFS.
Microsoft Certified Solutions Expert (MCSE), VMware Certified Professional (VCP), and ITIL Foundation.
Experience with enterprise-level backup products and storage technologies.

Don't worry if you don't tick all the boxes - if you meet most of them, we encourage you to submit your application.  We're most interested in your strengths, what you want to learn and how far you want to go.

Diverse Team Members, Shared Values and a Common Purpose

Providing our customers with smarter solutions takes an incredible team with diversity of thought, experience and perspectives driving innovation. Inclusion is at the heart of our culture and is one of our core values. It's about creating a workplace where everyone can do important work, feels welcome, valued, and respected, and has equal access to opportunities to thrive. Paul Chase - Chief Executive, Leidos Australia.

Leidos Australia is an equal opportunities organisation and is committed to creating a truly inclusive workplace. We welcome and encourage applications from Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islanders, culturally and linguistically diverse people, people with disabilities, veterans, neurodiverse people, and people of all genders, sexualities, and age groups.

Our five Advocacy Groups (Women and Allies Network, Young Professionals, Defence & Emergency Services, Action for Accessibility and Abilities and Pride+) provide an opportunity for team members to connect and collaborate on shared interests, and work to support and celebrate our diverse community.

Next Steps

To apply for this role, follow the links or apply via our Careers page.
Recruitment process - 1 virtual interview and/or 1 face-to-face & background checks.
Applicants may also need to meet International Traffic in Arms Regulations (ITAR) requirements. In certain circumstances this can place limitations on persons who hold dual nationality, permanent residency or are former nationals of certain countries as per ITAR 126.1.
We are committed to making our recruitment process accessible to all candidates. Please get in touch with our Careers team careers.au@au.leidos.com if you'd like to discuss any additional support during your application or throughout the recruitment process.

Are you ready to move beyond standard data center fit-outs and help build the physical backbone of a global AI cloud?

We are representing a world-leading technology firm that is making a multi-billion dollar investment in its global AI capabilities. They are urgently seeking experienced Data Center Designers for a mission-critical infrastructure expansion in Sydney and Melbourne.

This is a rare opportunity to join a high-priority, large-scale project from the ground up and in flight, contributing your expertise to a team that is shaping the future of cloud computing. This is a long-term contract role offering the chance to work on ground breaking projects of immense scale and complexity.

We are hiring for roles from Mid-Career to Lead level across their Sydney and Melbourne offices.

What you’ll be doing:
You will be responsible for creating and managing the design of data center white space, including rack layouts, power distribution, and network infrastructure for a major cloud platform. You will collaborate with internal stakeholders and co location providers to ensure engineering standards are met for this critical global project.

What you'll bring to the team:

Proven professional experience working in critical data center environments.
Experience creating design drawings using AutoCAD/Revit or similar tools.
Strong knowledge of data center electrical and mechanical infrastructure.
PUE experience
Experience MOPs/SOPs/EOPs for carrying out systems operations 
Understanding of BMS/EPMS control systems and data collection/trending.
What else is offered:

A 12-month initial contract with a strong likelihood of extension.
The opportunity to work on a globally significant AI infrastructure project.
Opportunity to get exposure to ground breaking large scale projects.
What's next:
If you're an experienced Data Center Designer looking for a challenging, long-term contract with a world-class team, APPLY NOW!

We can't wait to speak with you.

Job Title: Analytics Data Architect - New Microsoft Practice
Ad Text:
Analytics Data Architect – Azure

Our client: A global leader in technology consulting and digital transformation, partnering with major public sector and enterprise organisations across Australia to deliver secure, scalable, and future-ready cloud, data, and AI solutions.
They are currently seeking an experienced Analytics Data Architect (NV1 Cleared) to join their expanding Microsoft Azure practice, supporting high-impact data transformation programs across Government and Defence.
  
NV1 security clearance is essential.
  
The Role:

As the Analytics Data Architect, you will shape and implement end-to-end data architecture across Azure environments. This position plays a critical role in designing modern data platforms, improving data quality and accessibility, and ensuring secure, compliant delivery across complex Government programs.
  
You will:

Design and deliver Azure data architecture solutions, including ingestion, storage, processing, and analytics
• Develop and maintain enterprise-aligned data architecture frameworks, governance models, and security standards
• Work across Azure services including Microsoft Fabric, Data Lake, Azure Databricks, Data Factory, Synapse Analytics, Data Explorer, Cosmos DB, and Azure SQL
• Build and optimise scalable ETL and ELT pipelines using ADF and Synapse, including metadata ingestion and CI/CD automation
• Provide architectural oversight across integration, modelling, and analytics pipelines, ensuring performance, cost efficiency, and compliance
• Partner with data scientists and analysts to create high-quality data tools and reusable assets
• Implement strong data security, privacy, and governance controls across all Azure environments
• Produce technical architecture documentation, diagrams, and implementation roadmaps
• Drive continuous improvement using Microsoft WAF and CAF methodologies
Requirements:

• Active NV1 Security Clearance
• 10+ years’ experience across Data Architecture, Data Engineering, or Cloud Analytics
• Deep expertise in the Microsoft Azure analytics ecosystem, including Data Factory, Synapse, Databricks, Data Lake, Fabric, Cosmos DB, and Azure SQL
• Strong capability in data modelling, ETL design, and data warehousing
• Hands-on experience with PostgreSQL and Cosmos DB
• Strong understanding of enterprise cloud design, migration strategies, and technology governance
• Excellent communication and stakeholder engagement skills, with the ability to translate complex technical concepts into clear business value

 
Why you will love working here:

Work on nation-critical projects with a top-tier global systems integrator.
Be part of a fast-growing Azure & Data Analytics practice.
Access continuous learning, certifications, and leadership pathways.
Enjoy flexible work arrangements and an inclusive culture that values innovation and collaboration.
100% remote!

Overview

With more than 45,000 employees and partners worldwide, the Customer Experience and Success (CE&S) organization is on a mission to empower customers to accelerate business value through differentiated customer experiences that leverage Microsoft’s products and services, ignited by our people and culture. We drive cross-company alignment and execution, ensuring that we consistently exceed customers’ expectations in every interaction, whether in-product, digital, or human-centered. CE&S is responsible for all up services across the company, including consulting, customer success, and support across Microsoft’s portfolio of solutions and products. Join CE&S and help us accelerate AI transformation for our customers and the world.

We provide technical direction to our customers who are deploying, maintaining or innovating solutions using the latest technology.  We enable our customers to have the skills to deploy, support and maintain their Mission Critical environment in line with Microsoft recommended practices. 
We provide technical direction to our customers who are deploying, maintaining or innovating solutions using the latest technology.  We enable our customers to have the skills to deploy, support and maintain their Mission Critical environment in line with Microsoft recommended practices. 

Microsoft’s mission is to empower every person and every organization on the planet to achieve more. As employees we come together with a growth mindset, innovate to empower others and collaborate to realize our shared goals. Each day we build on our values of respect, integrity, and accountability to create a culture of inclusion where everyone can thrive at work and beyond.

Responsibilities

Participate in proactive account management, spot performance issues, analyze problems, develop solutions to meet customer needs, represent them.

Create deliverables to address common Microsoft Unified Support customer needs & support mobile-first, cloud-first strategy, share intellectual property with others.

Maintain, expand accreditations and certifications; assist in developing best practices for key technologies & products to support technical team readiness.

Consistently apply “lessons learned”, model personal accountability & teamwork.

Contribute & participate with meetings to articulate Microsoft Mission Critical Support offerings to all customers; share knowledge thru communities and adapt for customers.

We provide technical direction to our customers who are deploying, maintaining or innovating solutions using the latest technology.  

We enable our customers to have the skills to deploy, support and maintain their Mission Critical environment in line with Microsoft recommended practices. 

The ideal candidate will have the ability to combine their technical passion, creativity and customer focus to deliver great solutions to their customers and ensure they get the best out of our technologies and solutions. 

Qualifications

Required/minimum qualifications

Bachelor's Degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, Engineering, Business, Liberal Arts, or related field AND 4+ years experience in cloud/infrastructure technologies, information technology (IT) consulting/support, systems administration, network operations, software development/support, technology solutions, practice development, architecture, and/or consulting OR equivalent experience.

This position requires verification of Australian citizenship due to citizenship-based legal restrictions. Specifically, this position supports Australian government agency customers and is subject to certain citizenship-based restrictions where required or permitted by applicable law. To meet this legal requirement, and as a condition of employment, the successful candidate’s citizenship will be verified with a valid passport. 

Additional or preferred qualifications

Bachelor's Degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, Engineering, Business, Liberal Arts, or related field AND 8+ years experience in cloud/infrastructure technologies, information technology (IT) consulting/support, systems administration, network operations, software development/support, technology solutions, practice development, architecture, and/or consulting OR Master's Degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, Engineering, Business, Liberal Arts, or related field AND 6+ years experience in cloud/infrastructure technologies, technology solutions, practice development, architecture, and/or consulting OR equivalent experience.4+ years experience working in a customer-facing role (e.g., internal and/or external).4+ years experience working on technical projects.

Technical Certification in Cloud (e.g., Azure, Amazon Web Services, Google, security certifications). 

Identity:

Designing and implementing Active Directory and Azure Active Directory
integrating on-premises Active Directory with Azure AD (using eg. Azure AD Connect, Active Directory Federation Services)  

Experience with troubleshooting performance and replication issues on Domain Controllers along with client logon traffic problems and access to resources within domain and across trusts (involves creating and analyzing network traces and debug logs) 

Experience with domain name system (DNS), NTLM/Kerberos Authentication and Authorization via access token and access control list (ACL)

Good understanding of Group Policy Management and Infrastructure, certificates and public key infrastructure (PKI) and Distributed File System Namespace (DFSN)

Envision and deploy modern idntity solutions such as Azure AD MFA, Azure AD Conditional Access, Azure AD Privileged Identity Management, Azure AD B2B and Azure AD Application Proxy, Azure AD App Integration and Access Management, Access Reviews, Identity Protection, Defender for Identity, just-in-time administration, Password less authentication, user self-service capabilities.

Azure:

AVD

Azure Migrate + AVS

Azure Devops & Infrastructure as Code

Azure Landing Zones

Azure Networking 

Designing and implementing private, public and/or hybrid cloud solutions.

Designing, implementing, and securing resources including Azure Active Directory, Azure App Service Apps and Virtual Networks.

Designing networking and security solutions.

Creating and managing Azure Resource Manager (ARM) virtual machines.

Knowledge of or an interest in one or more of the following: Azure PowerShell, CLI, Visual Studio, Python, Ruby or Terraform

Additional experience needed

Ability to quickly build relationships and credibility with customers

A passion for learning about and experimenting with new technologies

Confidence in creating and delivering technical presentations, supportability reviews and training

Knowledge of problem resolution processes, triaging issues and a willingness to participate in post-incident meetings to share that knowledge

An interest in learning to read, interpret and/or develop technical specifications, action plans and support strategies

Ability to build trust to drive change with customers

Excellent organization and planning skills

We would also expect you to be able to pass the following Azure Certifications in the first 12 months of employment with us, if you do not already hold them:

AZ-900: Microsoft Azure Fundamentals

SC-300: Microsoft Identity and Access Administrator

This position will be open for a minimum of 5 days, with applications accepted on an ongoing basis until the position is filled.

Microsoft is an equal opportunity employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to age, ancestry, citizenship, color, family or medical care leave, gender identity or expression, genetic information, immigration status, marital status, medical condition, national origin, physical or mental disability, political affiliation, protected veteran or military status, race, ethnicity, religion, sex (including pregnancy), sexual orientation, or any other characteristic protected by applicable local laws, regulations and ordinances. If you need assistance with religious accommodations and/or a reasonable accommodation due to a disability during the application process, read more about requesting accommodations.

About GPS Electrical Services | Part of the Sentra Group

GPS Electrical Services is a specialist industrial electrical and automation provider delivering high-quality projects and maintenance across manufacturing, utilities, transport, food & beverage, pharmaceutical and other process-driven industries.

As part of the Sentra Group, we’re growing our automation capability and are seeking an Automation Engineer with 3+ years’ experience to join our Melbourne team.

The Opportunity

In this role, you will:

Design, develop and commission PLC and SCADA systems

Troubleshoot, support and optimise industrial automation systems

Assist with project planning, documentation, testing and integration

Collaborate with a highly skilled team across project design, integration and delivery

Contribute to client solutions that improve efficiency and safety

Participate in ongoing learning and development opportunities

About You

We’re looking for someone with:

2–3+ years’ experience in an automation or control systems engineering role

A Degree or Diploma in Engineering (Electrical, Mechatronics, Automation or similar)

Experience working in project environment for a Systems Integrator, OEM or End User

Excellent communication, critical thinking and problem-solving skills

Familiarity with various platforms across PLC, SCADA, motion control, robotics, or industrial networks

Experience with PLC/SCADA programming or commissioning

Familiarity with major platforms (Siemens, Allen-Bradley, Schneider)

Strong problem-solving and communication skills

A strong commitment to safety, quality and teamwork

Experience with Ignition (Inductive Automation) highly regarded

Why Join GPS?

Working with GPS means joining a supportive, values-driven team with a strong focus on career pathways enabling growth and development.

You’ll benefit from:

Meaningful, hands-on work across key Victorian industries

Competitive remuneration

Strong technical mentorship and ongoing development

A collaborative team culture backed by the Sentra Group

Work-life balance and a company that genuinely values its people

Our values guide how we work: Safety First, Genuinely Care, Do What’s Right, Expect to Learn and Innovate, and Collaborate Without Judgement.




If you’re an Automation Engineer looking to take the next step in your career, we’d love to hear from you.

Apply now through Seek or email careers@gpselec.com.au for more information.

Job Title: Principal Engineer (Data & AI Platform) - 6 Months Contract - AWS SageMaker
Ad Text:
Principal Engineer (Data & AI Platform) - 6 Months Rolling Contract - AWS SageMaker

About the company
Our client is a major Australian enterprise undergoing significant AI-driven transformation. The organisation is scaling its data and AI capability, investing in modern platforms, and building future-ready foundations to enable secure, enterprise-wide AI innovation.

About the role
This Principal Data Engineer role leads the hands-on build of a new AI and ML platform. Reporting to a Product Owner and working in a small cross-functional team, it drives platform engineering, architecture, delivery, and user enablement across the enterprise.

Benefits

Competitive daily rate
High-impact greenfield program
Opportunity to set enterprise AI platform standards
Flexible ways of working
Work with modern cloud-native technologies and emerging AI capability
Duties / Key responsibilities

Lead the build and operationalisation of the AI Workbench platform
Develop CI/CD, IaC, architecture artefacts, and scalable platform components
Provide technical leadership across cloud-native AI/ML services
Support user onboarding, platform adoption, optimisation, and performance
Mentor engineers and collaborate across architecture, security, and product teams

10+ years delivering large-scale data and AI/ML platforms
Expertise across AWS (SageMaker, Bedrock, S3, IAM) and cloud-native engineering

Experience establishing platform engineering standards in greenfield environments

Job Title: Delta V - Control Systems Engineer - Long Term Contract
Ad Text:
Great Opportunity for an individual with substantial DeltaV control system development experience

Reporting to the Engineering Manager you will work together with a great team to design / implement control system hardware and software architectures for custom automation projects.

Your experience will include

Tertiary qualifications in the field of engineering, software, business and/or project management.
Experience in DeltaV automation and PLC/HMI design.
Project planning, execution and delivery including managing control system project timelines, budget and work scope.
Knowledge and experience with industrial sensors, actuators and control equipment.
Familiarity with GMP manufacturing environment
Broad controls system experience enabling identifying appropriate solutions.
Understanding of other plant/facility IT/OT system components such as MES & Data Historians
Demonstrated problem solving ability
Excellent communication and interpersonal skills

If you are looking to work on an exciting large-scale, multi-year project with excellent remuneration then we want to speak to you.

Interested? APPLY NOW!!!

We are currently working with a QLD State Government Department to assist in the recruitment of a hands-on Data Engineer with strong experience in Microsoft Fabric (or related tool set) and Azure to design, build, and operate secure, reliable data pipelines and products within the emerging Enterprise Data Platform (EDP).



Your Role
The Data Engineer will join the Performance Monitoring and Reporting Unit to support the delivery of a high-profile program. The role partners closely with data governance (including Microsoft Purview) to deliver privacy-by-design ingestion, high-quality curated datasets, and performant semantic models for analytics and reporting. You will build ingestion and transformation across Bronze/Silver/Gold layers, run and interpret Purview scans, apply classifications, and automate deployment and monitoring so our data products are repeatable, auditable, and cost-effective.


Key Responsibilities:


Build and operate pipelines using Microsoft Fabric (Pipelines, Dataflows Gen2, Notebooks/Spark, Lakehouse/OneLake, SQL Endpoints) and relevant Azure services where required
Implement medallion architecture (Bronze/Silver/Gold), dimensional/semantic models for Power BI, and reusable data products aligned to enterprise standards
Execute and schedule metadata-only discovery in Microsoft Purview, apply classifications/sensitivity labels, register assets, and ensure lineage from source to insight
Implement data quality checks, validation rules, and automated tests; maintain technical docs, runbooks, and data dictionaries
Apply least-privilege access, managed identities, and masking/obfuscation where appropriate, ensuring separation of copy (ingestion) from use (purpose-based)
Use Git-based workflows and Azure DevOps (or equivalent) to version, test, and deploy pipelines, notebooks, and models, enabling parameterisation and environment promotion
Configure alerting, logging, and Operations dashboards; triage incidents; tune performance and storage; and optimise compute schedules
Work with data stewards, custodians, analysts, and product owners to deliver prioritised use cases


About You
We are looking for an analytical, detail-oriented professional who is comfortable operating in a fast-moving program context.



Essential Skills and Experience:


5+ years in data engineering (or equivalent), delivering production-grade pipelines and curated datasets in enterprise environments
Demonstrated experience with Microsoft Fabric (Pipelines/Dataflows Gen2/Notebooks, Lakehouse/OneLake, SQL Endpoints) and strong SQL and PySpark skills
Practical experience with Azure data services (e.g., Azure Data Factory/Synapse/Databricks-exposure acceptable if primary is Fabric)
Hands-on experience with Microsoft Purview: configuring/scheduling scans, managing collections, glossary/lineage, and applying classifications/sensitivity labels
Familiarity with medallion architecture (Bronze/Silver/Gold), dimensional modelling, and serving to Power BI
CI/CD experience with Azure DevOps (pipelines, environments, approvals); Infrastructure-as-Code exposure (Bicep/Terraform) is desirable
Strong grasp of security and privacy fundamentals (RBAC, managed identity, data masking, audit logging) and data quality practices
Experience working with governance teams, data stewards, and custodians, with clear written documentation and stakeholder communication skills


How to Apply: Click the Apply button or email to diane.sulayao@randstaddigital.com.au

At Randstad, we are passionate about providing equal employment opportunities and embracing diversity to the benefit of all. We actively encourage applications from any background.

Join a company that designs and owns all of its IP and are the gold standard in their space in Australia and global markets.

Collaborate directly with the CEO and senior leadership, playing a pivotal role in bridging customer, product, and commercial priorities.




THE COMPANY ​YOU'LL JOIN




Established over 25 years ago, our client is a specialist provider of vehicle compliance equipment and telematics solutions, with approximately half their business being export-based to the UK, Europe, and USA.

​The company designs and owns all of its IP across hardware, firmware and software, giving them an edge in customisation and technical flexibility.​

They've developed a competitive advantage through their ability to capture exceptionally detailed data points, enabling clients to solve complex problems in rail infrastructure, mining operations, and vehicle compliance sectors.

Their solutions allow clients to achieve significant operational benefits, including maintenance cost reduction, fleet optimisation, and improved safety compliance.​

They have strategically positioned themselves as a premium, quality-focused solution rather than competing with mass-market telematics providers.​

With significant untapped opportunities in their existing markets and potential for expansion into new sectors, they are now seeking to add a new role to the business.




THE IMPACT ​YOU'LL MAKE




Technical variety with customer impact
​You’ll bridge the gap between technology, product, and customer success — working hands-on with real-world vehicle systems while shaping how clients experience the solutions.​

Blend of autonomy and collaboration
​Work directly with the CEO and global BDMs, owning your projects end-to-end while collaborating closely with R&D, sales, and product teams across Australia and the US.​

Clear purpose and visibility
​You’ll be the key point ensuring every installation and onboarding runs smoothly — a role with tangible impact where success is seen and valued at the highest level.​

Exposure to global markets and next-gen tech
​Get involved in projects spanning Australia and the USA, supporting OEMs and major transport operators using CAN bus, telematics, and connected-vehicle data systems.​

Opportunity to shape product evolution
​You’ll gather customer feedback, identify pain points, and translate them into product improvements — influencing the roadmap and helping deliver smarter, more intuitive reporting tools.​

Growth in a high-trust, agile environment
​Join a small but fast-moving team that punches above its weight, values initiative, and rewards curiosity — ideal for someone who loves learning, problem-solving, and seeing ideas quickly become reality.


THE EXPERIENCE YOU'LL BRING

Experience in a hands-on technical role such as installation, integration, or customer support — ideally with telematics, fleet, or vehicle systems.​

Comfortable working across both hardware and software, able to spot issues and explain technical details clearly to customers.​

Enjoys a small, fast-moving environment, working closely with the CEO and senior team with plenty of freedom to make things happen.

ABOUT US
At Custom Fleet, we’ve been using our smarts to make the complex simple for over 40 years. It’s the driving force that continues to make us the fleet and leasing leader in Australia and New Zealand today.

When you join Custom Fleet, you’re joining a business that is Going Places. With us, what you do and who you are matter. Being part of our diverse crew means you’ll feel welcome, empowered, and have lots of fun celebrating our success (and that sure does feel good!). We are a crew of accountable go-getters on a journey of continuous improvement – we collaborate and support each other, working hard to win for our customers, for our business, and for each other. Whilst winning isn’t everything, we are proud of our success and love it when we reach the #1 spot.

ABOUT THE ROLE
We are looking for a Senior Data Engineer to join our growing team and help shape the future of our cloud-native data platform. This is a Greenfield role giving you the opportunity to design and build solutions from the ground up, influence architecture decisions and set best practices for the future.

In this role you will design and develop scalable ETL/ELT pipelines in Azure ensuring data is reliable, secure and ready to power insights across the business. You will collaborate with BI Developers, Analysts and stakeholders to deliver high-quality solutions that drive smarter decisions and better outcomes for our customers.

Essential Duties

Design and build scalable ETL/ELT pipelines to ingest, transform and load data into our Azure cloud data warehouse.

Develop and maintain data engineering solutions using Azure and selected cloud-based platforms and tools.

Collaborate with BI Developers, Analysts and Business Stakeholders to understand data requirements and deliver reliable solutions.

Implement data quality checks, monitoring and governance practices across pipelines.

Work with cross-functional teams (Architecture, Infrastructure, Security) to ensure alignment with enterprise standards.

Participate in all stages of the data engineering lifecycle: design, development, testing, deployment and documentation.

Other Duties

Shape and evolve the architecture of our cloud data platform, ensuring it scales with business growth.

Contribute to the development of best practices and reusable frameworks for data ingestion and transformation.

ABOUT YOU

Essential

Proven experience in cloud-based ETL/ELT development, ideally in Azure.

Strong proficiency in Python for data engineering tasks.

Hands-on experience with Databricks and Spark.

Solid understanding of data warehousing principles and best-practice modelling.

Ability to work independently and manage complexity in a dynamic environment.

Strong problem-solving skills and attention to detail.

Other

Experience with CI/CD pipelines.

Exposure to other cloud platforms and a range of data ingestion tools.

Familiarity with data governance and security frameworks.

Education & Experience

Essential

Minimum 5 years of experience in data engineering or related fields.

Tertiary qualification in Computer Science, Data Engineering or a related discipline.

Other

Experience with Databricks, Python, Azure Data Factory, and SQL Server is highly desirable.

Experience ingesting real-time data (telemetry data) would be a bonus.

FOR YOU

We offer industry leading 'Custom Perks' including:

Job Title: AI Specialist – LLMs, AI Agents & Automation (CRM Platform)
Ad Text:
Design and build the AI backbone of a next-generation digital service business.

We’re developing a hiCRMy automated, AI-driven delivery model and need an AI Specialist who can architect, build, and optimise LLM-powered agents and scalable workflow automations inside CRM.

This is a greenfield role with genuine ownership. You’ll shape the entire AI and automation ecosystem across our platform.







About Us

We operate a group of fast-growing digital businesses serving clients across Australia, New Zealand, and the USA. As we scale, we’re rebuilding our systems around intelligent AI, automation, and lean operations.

We move fast, and need people that can keep up and take real ownership their piece of the puzzle.







What You’ll Be Building

You’ll own major AI and automation projects that form the core of our future service model:

1. LLM-Powered AI Agents

Using OpenAI, embeddings, retrieval, and workflow logic, you’ll build specialised agents capable of:

answering domain-specific queries

processing internal knowledge

following multi-step reasoning

triggering actions inside CRM

2. Fully Automated Onboarding

A structured onboarding experience inside CRM that automatically:

assigns tasks

tracks progress

triggers emails/SMS/notifications

adapts to user behaviour

produces a personalised implementation plan

3. Operational AI Agents

Automation that reduces admin and increases precision:

lead review and routing

task creation and escalation

call/communication quality checks

progress oversight

workflow triggers across departments

4. Knowledge Base + Retrieval Engine

You’ll build the system that powers all intelligent responses, including:

ingestion of transcripts, videos, and documents

tagging and metadata structures

vector stores and embedding pipelines

retrieval logic for accuracy and relevance

5. System Integrations

Build and maintain data flows across platforms:

CRM ↔ OpenAI

CRM ↔ Stripe / Payments.ai

CRM ↔ Xero

Webhooks, APIs, and custom automations

Access control and error-proofing







Your Strengths

We are looking for someone who can think strategically and execute with precision.

Required:

Strong experience with OpenAI (agents, function calling, embeddings)

Demonstrated ability to build reliable AI chatbots or agents

Automation and workflow experience

API and webhook development capability

Experience with vector databases or embedding pipelines

Highly detail-driven and structured in documentation

Bonus:

Experience in productised services, SaaS, or digital programs

Background in automation engineering or data engineering

Familiarity with Stripe, Notion, Xero, Airtable, or Make/Zapier integrations







Why This Role Is Different

This isn’t a support role — you’re building the platform.

You’ll work directly with senior leadership, designing the architecture, delivering the systems, and shaping how our entire service model operates. If you want a role where your work becomes the core product, this is it.







How to Apply

Please provide:

Your CV

Examples of AI agents or automation projects you’ve built

A short summary of the most complex LLM workflow you’ve delivered

Links to GitHub, demos, or portfolio work (if available)
